title: Cloud Bar: Music Industry Education
description:
Veteran Music Executive / Music and Culture Writer, Naima Cochrane guides a series of conversations with experts in the music industry to help break down barriers for creators to enter the music business. 

Guests included Taz Taylor (Founder of Internet Money), Nick Mira (Producer-Internet Money), Moody Jones, (VP of Digital Creative at EMPIRE Records), Gabby Peluso (GM of Asylum Records), Chris Atlas (EVP of Urban Music and Marketing for Warner Records), Moe Shalizi (CEO, The Shalizi Group), Courtney Stewart (Founder of Right Hand Music Group, The Right Hand Foundation, and co-founder of Keep Cool Records) and Monee Perry (Co-President of Artistry Records/Artistry Group).

title: Cloud Bar: Hispanic Heritage Month
description:
Hispanic Heritage Month is here ‚Äî and we‚Äôre ready to celebrate Hispanic/Latinx artists and thought leaders who continue to impact, shape and influence the greater Latinx creative community. 

Hear in-depth discussions with industry insiders, learn about the issues on the minds of the Latinx creative community and more.

title: Cloud Bar: Music Discovery Today
description:
Hear music journalists, publicists, artists, and other prominent figures join @SoundCloud to talk about the impact of COVID-19 on their areas of the business and new approaches they‚Äôre developing, to meet the current challenges.

title: Cloud Bar: Live Music From A Distance
description:
With live events across the globe on hold or canceled, agents, managers, and others are facing unprecedented challenges. In these conversations, key figures in the live music space will discuss how they‚Äôre handling the rapid changes, how they‚Äôve continued to find ways to bring live events to fans through different platforms, and their thoughts on the future of ‚Äúlive‚Äù music.

Step into the neon-soaked underground of 1980s Miami as bizarre messages on your answering machine seem to be urging you to commit terrible acts of violence -- but will you obey? Hotline Miami overflows with raw brutality and skull crushing close combat as you find yourself outgunned and using your wits to choreograph your way through impossible situations. An unmistakable visual style, a driving soundtrack, and a surreal plot that will have you question your own thirst for blood. Bash and blast through over 20 multiscreen levels with 35 unique weapons and collect 25 game-altering masks in one of the darkest and most unusual independent games on the scene.

title: Alternative Rock
description:
In March 2019 I started these playlist with 77 tracks in. The next 17 months I looked steadily for new alternative tracks with a real catchy melody (sry., not excl. alt. rock songs)to add until the limit of 500 songs in one playlist. This was reached in August 2020.  By the way from time to time it could has happened that  a song was replaced by a even more catchy one.

I'm sure you will enjoy the selected songs. Each one with its own catchy melody which let  them become real earworms - in my ears -  all originated from the a alternative music genre. 
I hope the earworms will pocket you the same way as they did with me!  :)
